The paper deals with the optimization of an Energy Harvesting Device (EHD) in a Wireless Sensor Network (WSN) under real battery constraints. The problem is formulated as a Markov Decision Process, which falls under the category of control theory and optimization (cs.SY). The paper also considers imperfect knowledge of the state of charge of the battery and storage inefficiencies, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The optimization problem involves numerical computations, which are related to mathematical optimization (cs.MA) and machine learning (cs.LG).
